cases.sql: SELECT featurecla, name_en, ne_id, (ST_Area(geometry::geography) / 1000000.0) AS area_km2, geometry FROM ne_data.ne_10m_geography_regions_polys WHERE geometry IS NOT NULL AND (ST_Area(geometry::geography) / 1000000.0) > 500000 ORDER BY area_km2 DESC LIMIT 50;
reasoning: Selecting features by area (e.g., countries or subnational units) commonly applies to administrative boundary datasets where featurecla denotes country/admin types and large-area thresholds (500,000 km) identify large countries/units.

Featurecla can also represent geographic regions or landforms (regions, archipelagos, deserts); mapping entries >500,000 km may target these natural/region polygons, so this category covers non-administrative large-area features.
Contains the featurecla field required by the query.
Provides polygon geometries (geom) for regions/landforms so area filtering (>500,000 km) and mapping are possible.
Purpose-built for searching regions by category (featurecla) and spatial analyses, matching the task of mapping large feature classes.

cases.sql:
WITH continent_avg AS (
  SELECT continent, AVG(gdp_md)::double precision AS avg_gdp_md
  FROM ne_data.ne_10m_admin_0_countries_chn
  WHERE gdp_md IS NOT NULL AND continent IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY continent
)
SELECT
  t.formal_en,
  t.name,
  t.continent,
  t.gdp_md,
  ca.avg_gdp_md AS avg_gdp_md_continent,
  (t.gdp_md - ca.avg_gdp_md) AS gdp_minus_continent_avg,
  t.geometry
FROM ne_data.ne_10m_admin_0_countries_chn t
JOIN continent_avg ca ON t.continent = ca.continent
WHERE t.gdp_md IS NOT NULL
  AND t.continent IS NOT NULL
  AND t.gdp_md > ca.avg_gdp_md
ORDER BY gdp_minus_continent_avg DESC
LIMIT 50;
